; Example program that reads a line of text then prints it in reverse.

; Decrement value pointed to by data pointer by 10 (ASCII value of '\n').
btw btw btw btw btw btw btw btw btw btw

; Keep reading into working memory until a new line character is encountered.
the
    ; Increment value pointed to by data pointer back to its original value.
    bored bored bored bored bored bored bored bored bored bored
    ; Read a character into the next byte of memory.
    i by
    ; Decrement it by 10 ('\n') so that when we read a new line, the value
    ; pointed to by the data pointer at the end of the loop iteration will be 0,
    ; and the loop will stop.
    btw btw btw btw btw btw btw btw btw btw
way

; Print the line in reverse.
am the btw am way

; Print new line.
bored bored bored bored bored bored bored bored bored bored btw
